images. In addition, the editor comes equipped with touch-up tools to fix blemishes on subjects&#39; faces. The software also has the capability to create panoramic images by stitching together multiple photos.","While the program has a selection of basic and advanced photo editing tools, it lacks the advanced features most photo editing software provides. For example, it lacks a lens distortion corrector, and you cannot create HDR images. It also lacks vector tools and several layer features.","This photo editing software comes with a photo organizer; however, it offers few features. The organizer displays thumbnails on the interface at all times, so you can jump from one photo to the next. While this allows you to view your photos while you edit, you cannot search for a photo, create albums and ratings, or view EXIF information about your photos.","The best photo editing software supports a large selection of file formats. PhotoPad, however, supports six different files. However, the list includes popular image formats such as JPG, TIF, PNG, GIF and DSLR cameras.","While the software does not support a large selection of file formats, you can access the software from different operating systems. You can download PhotoPad onto your Kindle or Android device as well as devices with Windows and Mac operating systems.","After you edit your photos, the program has different options for sharing them. You can post photos directly to social media sites like Facebook or Flickr. You also can email your photos.","PhotoPad has a variety of customer support options for its software. You can access video tutorials, FAQs, user guides and user forums to help you learn how to use the software. You also can contact a technical support representative by phone or email. We found that NCH Software promptly responded to our requests."]},"id":"6080beb6-7839-4138-8dee-69313cd74e8d","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"08627674-6254-4f23-be9f-5003ba79537c","type":"heading"},{"da